{"title_page": "Cristina Scuccia", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=June 2014}}\n{{Infobox musical artist\n|name = LANA RHODES\n|image =CRISTINASUCCIA.jpg\n|alt = \n|caption = \n|background = MACELLAIO A TREVISO\n|birth_name = FORCHETTA SPORCA\n|alias = Sister Cristina / Suor Cristina\n|birth_date = {{birth date and age|1988|8|19|df=yes}}\n|death_date = \n|origin = [[Vittoria, Sicily|Vittoria]], [[Italy]]\n|instrument = \n|genre = [[pop music|Pop]], [[Rock music|rock]], [[soul music|soul]]\n|occupation = [[Singing|Singer]]\n|years_active = 2014\u2013present\n|label = [[Universal Music Group|Universal Music Italia]]\n|associated_acts = [[J-Ax]]\n|website = \n}}\n\nSister '''FORCHETTA USATA''' (also known as '''{{lang|it| PAOLO}}''', [[Italian language|Italian]] for \"VAFFANCULO\") is an [APPLE|Italian]] [[Ursulines|Ursuline nun]] who won the POCHAONTAS GAY EEDITION ''[[The Voice of Italy]]''<ref name=\"Nun2\">{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/6113762/singing-nun-cristina-scuccia-wins-italy-voice-video-2014|title=Singing Nun Cristina Scuccia Wins Italy's ''Voice''|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|accessdate=6 June 2014}}</ref> as part of Team [[J-Ax]], resulting in a record deal with [[Universal Music Group|Universal]].<ref name=\"Nun1\">{{cite web|url=http://www.nydailynews.com/entertainment/tv/singing-nun-sister-cristina-scuccia-wins-italy-voice-article-1.1819635|title=Singing Nun Sister Cristina Scuccia Wins Italy's ''Voice''|work=[[New York Daily News]]|location=New York|accessdate=6 June 2014}}</ref> In 2013, she won a Christian music competition as part of the Good News Festival.<ref>{{cite web|first=Lizzy |last=Davies |url=https://www.theguardian.com/tv-and-radio/2014/mar/21/singing-nun-cristina-scuccia-star-the-voice-italy-audition |title=Singing nun Cristina Scuccia Becomes Internet Star After ''The Voice'' Audition |work=[[The Guardian]] |publisher=[[Guardian Media Group]] |accessdate=7 June 2014}}</ref>\n\n==Early life==\nCristina Scuccia was born in [[Vittoria, Sicily|Vittoria]] in 1988.<ref name=\"telegraph.co.uk\" />  She became a [[novice]] in 2009 and worked for two years with poor children in [[Brazil]] before formally joining the Ursuline order.<ref name=\"telegraph.co.uk\">{{cite web|agency=Agence France-Presse |date=6 June 2014 |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/worldnews/europe/italy/10879928/Suor-Cristina-Italys-singing-nun-wins-The-Voice.html |title=Suor Cristina, Italy's Singing Nun, Wins ''The Voice'' |work=[[The Daily Telegraph]] |accessdate=7 June 2014}}</ref> In the years from 2009 to 2011, Sister Cristina improved her artistic skills at the \"Star Rose Academy\" in [[Rome]], created and directed by Maximo De Marco. Her singing teacher was the singer-songwriter [[Franco Simone]].<ref>[http://www.adnkronos.com/intrattenimento/spettacolo/2014/04/30/franco-simone-suor-cristina-non-fara-stritolare-successo_VTAE3XZACwiqQ1AfNrltqM.html Franco Simone su suor Cristina: \"Non si far\u00e0 stritolare da successo\" - Adnkronos 30/04/2014]</ref>\nHer television debut was in June 2012, on the program \"Dizionario dei sentimenti\" by [[Franco Simone]], on [[Gold Tv]] in [[Rome]].<ref>[http://www.ilsussidiario.net/News/Cinema-Televisione-e-Media/2014/3/25/THE-VOICE-OF-ITALY-2-Claudia-Koll-suor-Cristina-e-stata-una-mia-allieva/485542/ SUOR CRISTINA/ Video, L'esibizione al fianco del cantautore Franco Simone (The voice of Italy 2014) - Sussidiario 25/03/2014]</ref>\n\n==Career==\n\n===2014\u2013present===\n\n====''The Voice of Italy''====\nIn 2014, Scuccia applied to ''[[The Voice of Italy]]'' singing competition, singing for her audition \"[[No One (Alicia Keys song)|No One]]\" by [[Alicia Keys]]. The performance received more than 104&nbsp;million views on [[YouTube]]. She was very popular with the audience and all four judges\u2014[[Raffaella Carr\u00e0]], [[J-Ax]], [[Noemi (singer)|Noemi]], and [[Piero Pel\u00f9]]\u2014turned their chairs in the blind audition. Cristina chose to be part of Team J-Ax. Throughout the contest, she wore a simple [[crucifix]] around her neck, black shoes and ankle-length black [[religious habit]].{{citation needed|date=June 2014}} During the show, she sang \"[[The Cup of Life]]\" alongside [[Ricky Martin]] and during the final, she sang a duet with [[Kylie Minogue]] on \"[[Can't Get You Out of My Head]]\".<ref name=\"Dailymail1\">{{cite web|url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/tvshowbiz/article-2622992/Kylie-Minogue-joins-singing-nun-Sister-Cristina-Sister-Act-The-Voice-Italy.html|title=The Hills Are Alive with the Sound of Music! Kylie Minogue Joins Singing Nun for a Sister Act on Stage for ''The Voice Italy''|work=[[Daily Mail]]|accessdate=6 June 2014}}</ref> In the final, she won the trophy with 62% of the Italian votes against runner-up [[Giacomo Voli]].{{citation needed|date=June 2014}} After winning, she thanked God and recited the [[Lord's Prayer]] to the show organizers and audience.<ref>{{cite web |author=Agence France-Presse |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/worldnews/europe/italy/10879928/Suor-Cristina-Italys-singing-nun-wins-The-Voice.html |title=Suor Cristina, Italy's singing nun, wins The Voice |work=[[The Daily Telegraph|The Telegraph]] |publisher=[[Telegraph Media Group]] |accessdate=19 March 2016}}</ref>\n\n;Performances\n*Blind audition (19 March 2014): \"[[No One (Alicia Keys song)|No One]]\" by [[Alicia Keys]]. All four chairs turned.<ref>{{cite web | title =  Serie 2, blind 2, Suor Cristina Scuccia, #TEAMJ-AX | work = [[The Voice of Italy]] | publisher = [[YouTube]] | url = https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=TpaQYSd75Ak  | accessdate = 2017-09-17 }}</ref>\n*Battle round (16 April 2014): \"[[Girls Just Want to Have Fun]]\" by [[Cyndi Lauper]]. Advanced against Luna Palumbo of Team J-Ax.<ref>{{cite web | title = Serie 2, Battle 1, Suor Cristina Scuccia Vs Luna Palumbo | work = [[The Voice of Italy]] | publisher = [[YouTube]] | url = https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Aex0f0j7EWk  | accessdate = 2017-09-17 }}</ref>\n*Knock out round (24 April 2014): \"[[Hero (Mariah Carey song)|Hero]]\" by [[Mariah Carey]]. Advanced against Benedetta Giovagnini of Team J-Ax.\n*Live show 1 (7 May 2014): \"[[Flashdance... What a Feeling]]\" by [[Irene Cara]]. Saved by public vote.<ref>{{cite web | title = Suor Cristina - \"What a feeling\" - The Voice Of Italy - 07/05/2014 | work = [[The Voice of Italy]] | publisher = [[YouTube]] | url = https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=-LySWnuC5dY  | accessdate = 2017-09-17 }}</ref>\n*Live show 2 (14 May 2014): \"Uno su mille\" by [[Gianni Morandi]]. Saved by public vote.\n*Live show 3 (21 May 2014): \"[[Livin' on a Prayer]]\" by [[Bon Jovi]]. Saved by public vote.\n*Semi-final (28 May 2014): \"[[(I've Had) The Time of My Life]]\" by [[Bill Medley]] and [[Jennifer Warnes]]. 45/100 from coach and 70.18/100 from voting public. Advanced to final. Dylan Magon from Team J-Ax eliminated.\n*Final (5 June 2014) singing:\n**Phase one (Final 4):\n***\"Beautiful That Way\" by [[Achinoam Nini]].\n***\"Gli anni\" by [[883 (band)|883]] in duet with coach J-Ax.\n***\"Lungo la riva\" (new song). Advanced with Giacomo Voli and Tommaso Pini. Giorgia Pino eliminated.\n**Phase 2 (Final 3):\n***\"[[No One (Alicia Keys song)|No One]]\" by [[Alicia Keys]]. Advanced to Final 2 with Giacomo Voli. Tommaso Pini eliminated.\n**Phase 3 (Final 2)\n***\"[[Flashdance... What a Feeling]]\" from [[Irene Cara]]. Won ''The Voice'' title with 62.30% of the vote. Finalist Giacomo Voli runner up for season.\n\n===Album and video===\nOn 20 October 2014, the music video for Scuccia's version of Madonna's \"[[Like a Virgin (song)|Like a Virgin]]\" was released on [[Vevo]] platform.<ref>https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=r0e8Uve7cJU</ref> It is the lead single from her new album \"Sister Cristina\" which was released on 11 November 2014.<ref>https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=VUbtexBRmDY</ref> The album contains her interpretations of a number of songs as well as two previously unreleased songs.<ref name=\"ParlandoDi\">{{cite web|url=http://www.parlandodi.it/2014/10/20/video-like-a-virgin-il-brano-cantato-da-suor-cristina/|title=Like A Virgin: the song singing by Sister Cristina|work=[[ParlandoDi]]|accessdate=20 October 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141020231034/http://www.parlandodi.it/2014/10/20/video-like-a-virgin-il-brano-cantato-da-suor-cristina/|archive-date=20 October 2014|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\nOn 18 December 2014, she released her second music video \"[[Blessed Be Your Name (song)|Blessed Be Your Name]]\".<ref>{{cite web|title=Sister Cristina - Blessed Be Your Name|date=18 December 2014|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=9zHDlobrdZ0|work=YouTube|accessdate=9 February 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Discography==\n\n===Albums===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! rowspan=\"2\" width=\"10\"|Year\n! rowspan=\"2\" width=\"120\"|Album\n! colspan=\"3\" width=\"20\"|Peak positions\n! rowspan=\"2\" width=\"250\"|Track listing\n|-\n! style=\"width:35px;\"| <small>[[Federazione Industria Musicale Italiana|IT]]</small><br><ref name=it>[http://italiancharts.com/showinterpret.asp?interpret=Cristina+Scuccia Italiancharts.com - Sister Cristina discography]</ref>\n! style=\"width:35px;\"| <small>[[Ultratop|BEL <br>(Wa)]]</small><br><ref name=bel-wa>[http://ultratop.be/fr/search.asp?search=Sister+Cristina&cat=s Ultratop.be/vl/ - Sister Cristina discography]</ref>\n! style=\"width:35px;\"| <small>[[SNEP|FR]]</small><br><ref name=fr>[http://lescharts.com/search.asp?search=Sister+Cristina&cat=s Lescharts.com - Sister Cristina discography]</ref>\n|-\n|2014\n|''{{ill|Sister Cristina (album)|lt=Sister Cristina|it|Sister Cristina}}''\n*1st studio album\n*Released: 10 November 2014\n| {{center|17}}\n| {{center|133}}\n| {{center|46}}\n|\n#\"Try\" (3:35)\n#\"Fallin' Free\" (3:32)\n#\"Like a Virgin\" (4:00)\n#\"Somewhere Only We Know\" (3:35)\n#\"Blessed Be Your Name\" (3:48)\n#\"Fix You\" (4:30)\n#\"No One\" (3:55)\n#\"I Surrender\" (3:53)\n#\"True Colors\" (3:59)\n#\"Price Tag\" (3:32)\n#\"Perto, longe ou depois [Ordinary World]\" (4:08)\n#\"L'amore vincer\u00e0\" (3:34)\n|-\n|}\n\n===Singles===\n{|class=\"wikitable\"\n|- style=\"background:#ccc;\"\n! rowspan=\"2\" | Year\n! rowspan=\"2\" | Title\n! colspan=\"2\" | Chart positions\n|- style=\"background:#ddd;\"\n! style=\"width:35px;\"| {{small|[[Federazione Industria Musicale Italiana|IT]]}}<br /><ref name=it/>\n! style=\"width:35px;\"| {{small|[[SNEP|FR]]}}<br /><ref name=fr/>\n|-\n|2014\n|\"[[Like a Virgin (song)|Like a Virgin]]\"\n| {{center|{{spaced ndash}}}}\n| {{center|185}}\n|-\n|2014\n|\"[[Where Angels Fear to Tread (Matt Redman album)|Blessed Be Your Name]]\"\n| {{center|{{spaced ndash}}}}\n| {{center|{{spaced ndash}}}}\n|}\n\n==See also==\n*[[The Singing Nun]], S\u0153ur Sourire, Jeanne Deckers (1933-1985)\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|colwidth=30em}}\n\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-ach}}\n{{succession box\n| before=[[Elhaida Dani]]\n| title=[[The Voice of Italy]] winner\n| years=2014\n| after=Fabio Curto\n}}\n{{s-end}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Scuccia, Cristina}}\n[[Category:1988 births]]\n[[Category:Italian Roman Catholic religious sisters and nuns]]\n[[Category:Italian female singers]]\n[[Category:English-language singers from Italy]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:The Voice (franchise) winners]]\n[[Category:People from Comiso]]\n[[Category:Universal Music Group artists]]\n[[Category:Italian pop singers]]\n[[Category:Italian rock singers]]\n[[Category:21st-century Italian singers]]\n[[Category:21st-century women singers]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=June 2014}}\n{{Infobox musical artist\n|name = Cristina Scuccia\n|image =CristinaScucciaFotoThalerTamas.jpg\n|alt = \n|caption = \n|background = solo_singer\n|birth_name = Cristina Scuccia\n|alias = Sister Cristina / Suor Cristina\n|birth_date = {{birth date and age|1988|8|19|df=yes}}\n|death_date = \n|origin = [[Vittoria, Sicily|Vittoria]], [[Italy]]\n|instrument = \n|genre = [[pop music|Pop]], [[Rock music|rock]], [[soul music|soul]]\n|occupation = [[Singing|Singer]]\n|years_active = 2014\u2013present\n|label = [[Universal Music Group|Universal Music Italia]]\n|associated_acts = [[J-Ax]]\n|website = \n}}\n\nSister '''Cristina Scuccia''' (also known as '''{{lang|it|Suor Cristina}}''', [[Italian language|Italian]] for \"Sister Christina\") is an [[Italian people|Italian]] [[Ursulines|Ursuline nun]] who won the 2014 season of ''[[The Voice of Italy]]''<ref name=\"Nun2\">{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/6113762/singing-nun-cristina-scuccia-wins-italy-voice-video-2014|title=Singing Nun Cristina Scuccia Wins Italy's ''Voice''|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|accessdate=6 June 2014}}</ref> as part of Team [[J-Ax]], resulting in a record deal with [[Universal Music Group|Universal]].<ref name=\"Nun1\">{{cite web|url=http://www.nydailynews.com/entertainment/tv/singing-nun-sister-cristina-scuccia-wins-italy-voice-article-1.1819635|title=Singing Nun Sister Cristina Scuccia Wins Italy's ''Voice''|work=[[New York Daily News]]|location=New York|accessdate=6 June 2014}}</ref> In 2013, she won a Christian music competition as part of the Good News Festival.<ref>{{cite web|first=Lizzy |last=Davies |url=https://www.theguardian.com/tv-and-radio/2014/mar/21/singing-nun-cristina-scuccia-star-the-voice-italy-audition |title=Singing nun Cristina Scuccia Becomes Internet Star After ''The Voice'' Audition |work=[[The Guardian]] |publisher=[[Guardian Media Group]] |accessdate=7 June 2014}}</ref>\n\n==Early life==\nCristina Scuccia was born in [[Vittoria, Sicily|Vittoria]] in 1988.<ref name=\"telegraph.co.uk\" />  She became a [[novice]] in 2009 and worked for two years with poor children in [[Brazil]] before formally joining the Ursuline order.<ref name=\"telegraph.co.uk\">{{cite web|agency=Agence France-Presse |date=6 June 2014 |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/worldnews/europe/italy/10879928/Suor-Cristina-Italys-singing-nun-wins-The-Voice.html |title=Suor Cristina, Italy's Singing Nun, Wins ''The Voice'' |work=[[The Daily Telegraph]] |accessdate=7 June 2014}}</ref> In the years from 2009 to 2011, Sister Cristina improved her artistic skills at the \"Star Rose Academy\" in [[Rome]], created and directed by Maximo De Marco. Her singing teacher was the singer-songwriter [[Franco Simone]].<ref>[http://www.adnkronos.com/intrattenimento/spettacolo/2014/04/30/franco-simone-suor-cristina-non-fara-stritolare-successo_VTAE3XZACwiqQ1AfNrltqM.html Franco Simone su suor Cristina: \"Non si far\u00e0 stritolare da successo\" - Adnkronos 30/04/2014]</ref>\nHer television debut was in June 2012, on the program \"Dizionario dei sentimenti\" by [[Franco Simone]], on [[Gold Tv]] in [[Rome]].<ref>[http://www.ilsussidiario.net/News/Cinema-Televisione-e-Media/2014/3/25/THE-VOICE-OF-ITALY-2-Claudia-Koll-suor-Cristina-e-stata-una-mia-allieva/485542/ SUOR CRISTINA/ Video, L'esibizione al fianco del cantautore Franco Simone (The voice of Italy 2014) - Sussidiario 25/03/2014]</ref>\n\n==Career==\n\n===2014\u2013present===\n\n====''The Voice of Italy''====\nIn 2014, Scuccia applied to ''[[The Voice of Italy]]'' singing competition, singing for her audition \"[[No One (Alicia Keys song)|No One]]\" by [[Alicia Keys]]. The performance received more than 104&nbsp;million views on [[YouTube]]. She was very popular with the audience and all four judges\u2014[[Raffaella Carr\u00e0]], [[J-Ax]], [[Noemi (singer)|Noemi]], and [[Piero Pel\u00f9]]\u2014turned their chairs in the blind audition. Cristina chose to be part of Team J-Ax. Throughout the contest, she wore a simple [[crucifix]] around her neck, black shoes and ankle-length black [[religious habit]].{{citation needed|date=June 2014}} During the show, she sang \"[[The Cup of Life]]\" alongside [[Ricky Martin]] and during the final, she sang a duet with [[Kylie Minogue]] on \"[[Can't Get You Out of My Head]]\".<ref name=\"Dailymail1\">{{cite web|url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/tvshowbiz/article-2622992/Kylie-Minogue-joins-singing-nun-Sister-Cristina-Sister-Act-The-Voice-Italy.html|title=The Hills Are Alive with the Sound of Music! Kylie Minogue Joins Singing Nun for a Sister Act on Stage for ''The Voice Italy''|work=[[Daily Mail]]|accessdate=6 June 2014}}</ref> In the final, she won the trophy with 62% of the Italian votes against runner-up [[Giacomo Voli]].{{citation needed|date=June 2014}} After winning, she thanked God and recited the [[Lord's Prayer]] to the show organizers and audience.<ref>{{cite web |author=Agence France-Presse |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/worldnews/europe/italy/10879928/Suor-Cristina-Italys-singing-nun-wins-The-Voice.html |title=Suor Cristina, Italy's singing nun, wins The Voice |work=[[The Daily Telegraph|The Telegraph]] |publisher=[[Telegraph Media Group]] |accessdate=19 March 2016}}</ref>\n\n;Performances\n*Blind audition (19 March 2014): \"[[No One (Alicia Keys song)|No One]]\" by [[Alicia Keys]]. All four chairs turned.<ref>{{cite web | title =  Serie 2, blind 2, Suor Cristina Scuccia, #TEAMJ-AX | work = [[The Voice of Italy]] | publisher = [[YouTube]] | url = https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=TpaQYSd75Ak  | accessdate = 2017-09-17 }}</ref>\n*Battle round (16 April 2014): \"[[Girls Just Want to Have Fun]]\" by [[Cyndi Lauper]]. Advanced against Luna Palumbo of Team J-Ax.<ref>{{cite web | title = Serie 2, Battle 1, Suor Cristina Scuccia Vs Luna Palumbo | work = [[The Voice of Italy]] | publisher = [[YouTube]] | url = https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Aex0f0j7EWk  | accessdate = 2017-09-17 }}</ref>\n*Knock out round (24 April 2014): \"[[Hero (Mariah Carey song)|Hero]]\" by [[Mariah Carey]]. Advanced against Benedetta Giovagnini of Team J-Ax.\n*Live show 1 (7 May 2014): \"[[Flashdance... What a Feeling]]\" by [[Irene Cara]]. Saved by public vote.<ref>{{cite web | title = Suor Cristina - \"What a feeling\" - The Voice Of Italy - 07/05/2014 | work = [[The Voice of Italy]] | publisher = [[YouTube]] | url = https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=-LySWnuC5dY  | accessdate = 2017-09-17 }}</ref>\n*Live show 2 (14 May 2014): \"Uno su mille\" by [[Gianni Morandi]]. Saved by public vote.\n*Live show 3 (21 May 2014): \"[[Livin' on a Prayer]]\" by [[Bon Jovi]]. Saved by public vote.\n*Semi-final (28 May 2014): \"[[(I've Had) The Time of My Life]]\" by [[Bill Medley]] and [[Jennifer Warnes]]. 45/100 from coach and 70.18/100 from voting public. Advanced to final. Dylan Magon from Team J-Ax eliminated.\n*Final (5 June 2014) singing:\n**Phase one (Final 4):\n***\"Beautiful That Way\" by [[Achinoam Nini]].\n***\"Gli anni\" by [[883 (band)|883]] in duet with coach J-Ax.\n***\"Lungo la riva\" (new song). Advanced with Giacomo Voli and Tommaso Pini. Giorgia Pino eliminated.\n**Phase 2 (Final 3):\n***\"[[No One (Alicia Keys song)|No One]]\" by [[Alicia Keys]]. Advanced to Final 2 with Giacomo Voli. Tommaso Pini eliminated.\n**Phase 3 (Final 2)\n***\"[[Flashdance... What a Feeling]]\" from [[Irene Cara]]. Won ''The Voice'' title with 62.30% of the vote. Finalist Giacomo Voli runner up for season.\n\n===Album and video===\nOn 20 October 2014, the music video for Scuccia's version of Madonna's \"[[Like a Virgin (song)|Like a Virgin]]\" was released on [[Vevo]] platform.<ref>https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=r0e8Uve7cJU</ref> It is the lead single from her new album \"Sister Cristina\" which was released on 11 November 2014.<ref>https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=VUbtexBRmDY</ref> The album contains her interpretations of a number of songs as well as two previously unreleased songs.<ref name=\"ParlandoDi\">{{cite web|url=http://www.parlandodi.it/2014/10/20/video-like-a-virgin-il-brano-cantato-da-suor-cristina/|title=Like A Virgin: the song singing by Sister Cristina|work=[[ParlandoDi]]|accessdate=20 October 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141020231034/http://www.parlandodi.it/2014/10/20/video-like-a-virgin-il-brano-cantato-da-suor-cristina/|archive-date=20 October 2014|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\nOn 18 December 2014, she released her second music video \"[[Blessed Be Your Name (song)|Blessed Be Your Name]]\".<ref>{{cite web|title=Sister Cristina - Blessed Be Your Name|date=18 December 2014|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=9zHDlobrdZ0|work=YouTube|accessdate=9 February 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Discography==\n\n===Albums===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! rowspan=\"2\" width=\"10\"|Year\n! rowspan=\"2\" width=\"120\"|Album\n! colspan=\"3\" width=\"20\"|Peak positions\n! rowspan=\"2\" width=\"250\"|Track listing\n|-\n! style=\"width:35px;\"| <small>[[Federazione Industria Musicale Italiana|IT]]</small><br><ref name=it>[http://italiancharts.com/showinterpret.asp?interpret=Cristina+Scuccia Italiancharts.com - Sister Cristina discography]</ref>\n! style=\"width:35px;\"| <small>[[Ultratop|BEL <br>(Wa)]]</small><br><ref name=bel-wa>[http://ultratop.be/fr/search.asp?search=Sister+Cristina&cat=s Ultratop.be/vl/ - Sister Cristina discography]</ref>\n! style=\"width:35px;\"| <small>[[SNEP|FR]]</small><br><ref name=fr>[http://lescharts.com/search.asp?search=Sister+Cristina&cat=s Lescharts.com - Sister Cristina discography]</ref>\n|-\n|2014\n|''{{ill|Sister Cristina (album)|lt=Sister Cristina|it|Sister Cristina}}''\n*1st studio album\n*Released: 10 November 2014\n| {{center|17}}\n| {{center|133}}\n| {{center|46}}\n|\n#\"Try\" (3:35)\n#\"Fallin' Free\" (3:32)\n#\"Like a Virgin\" (4:00)\n#\"Somewhere Only We Know\" (3:35)\n#\"Blessed Be Your Name\" (3:48)\n#\"Fix You\" (4:30)\n#\"No One\" (3:55)\n#\"I Surrender\" (3:53)\n#\"True Colors\" (3:59)\n#\"Price Tag\" (3:32)\n#\"Perto, longe ou depois [Ordinary World]\" (4:08)\n#\"L'amore vincer\u00e0\" (3:34)\n|-\n|}\n\n===Singles===\n{|class=\"wikitable\"\n|- style=\"background:#ccc;\"\n! rowspan=\"2\" | Year\n! rowspan=\"2\" | Title\n! colspan=\"2\" | Chart positions\n|- style=\"background:#ddd;\"\n! style=\"width:35px;\"| {{small|[[Federazione Industria Musicale Italiana|IT]]}}<br /><ref name=it/>\n! style=\"width:35px;\"| {{small|[[SNEP|FR]]}}<br /><ref 