09\u201310 DFB-Pokal|2009\u201310]], [[2012\u201313 DFB-Pokal|2012\u201313]], [[2013\u201314 DFB-Pokal|2013\u201314]], [[2015\u201316 DFB-Pokal|2015\u201316]], [[2018\u201319 DFB-Pokal|2018\u201319]]\n* [[DFL-Supercup]]: [[2010 DFL-Supercup|2010]], [[2012 DFL-Supercup|2012]], [[2016 DFL-Supercup|2016]], [[2017 DFL-Supercup|2017]], [[2018 DFL-Supercup|2018]]\n* [[UEFA Champions League]]: [[2012\u201313 UEFA Champions League|2012\u201313]]\n* [[UEFA Super Cup]]: [[2013 UEFA Super Cup|2013]]\n* [[FIFA Club World Cup]]: [[2013 FIFA Club World Cup|2013]]\n\n'''Germany'''\n* [[FIFA World Cup]]: [[2014 FIFA World Cup|2014]]<ref name=\"Soccerway\" /> Third place: [[2010 FIFA World Cup|2010]]<ref>{{cite web | url = http://edition.cnn.com/2010/SPORT/football/07/10/world.cup.uruguay.germany/index.html | title = Khedira's late winner gives Germany third place at World Cup | website = CNN | access-date = 22 September 2018}}</ref>\n\n'''Individual'''\n*[[DFB-Pokal]] Top Goalscorer: [[2009\u201310 DFB-Pokal|2009\u201310]], [[2013\u201314 DFB-Pokal|2013\u201314]]\n*[[FIFA World Cup 2010|FIFA World Cup 2010 Man of the Match]]: [[Germany v England (2010)#Germany vs England|vs. England]], [[2010 FIFA World Cup knockout stage#Third place play-off|vs. Uruguay]]\n*[[FIFA World Cup 2014|FIFA World Cup 2014 Man of the Match]]: [[2014 FIFA World Cup group stage#group|vs. Portugal]], [[2014 FIFA World Cup group stage#group stage|vs. United States]]\n*[[FIFA World Cup awards#Golden Boot|FIFA World Cup Golden Boot]]: [[2010 FIFA World Cup|2010]]<ref name=\"goldenboot2010\" />\n*[[FIFA World Cup awards#Silver Boot|FIFA World Cup Silver Boot]]: [[2014 FIFA World Cup|2014]]<ref name=FIFAWCSB&SB /><ref name=FIFAWCSB&SB2 />\n*[[FIFA World Cup awards#Best Young Player Award|FIFA World Cup Best Young Player]]: [[2010 FIFA World Cup|2010]]<ref name=\"youngplayer2010\" />\n*[[FIFA World Cup 2010]] Most assists (shared with [[Mesut \u00d6zil]], [[Bastian Schweinsteiger]], [[Kak\u00e1]], and [[Dirk Kuyt]])\n*Bayerischer Sportpreis: 2010<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sportpreis.bayern.de/infos_content_preistraeger.htm|title=Alle Preistr\u00e4ger|language=German|publisher=Bayerischer Sportpreis|accessdate=19 December 2010|trans-title=All award winners}}</ref>\n*[[Silbernes Lorbeerblatt]]: 2010,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rp-online.de/sport/fussball/nationalelf/wm/dfb/DFB-Elf-erhaelt-Silbernes-Lorbeerblatt_bid_59101.html|title=DFB-Elf erh\u00e4lt Silbernes Lorbeerblatt|accessdate=19 December 2010|language=German|publisher=[[Rheinische Post]]}}</ref> 2014<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.t-online.de/sport/fussball/id_71733490/gauck-zeichnet-nationalmannschaft-mit-dem-silbernen-lorbeerblatt-aus.html|title=Gauck zeichnet vorbildliche Weltmeister aus| date = 10 November 2014|language=German|publisher = [[T-Online]] | accessdate = 29 November 2014}}</ref>\n* [[Bavarian Order of Merit]]: 2019<ref>{{cite web | url = https://fcbayern.com/en/news/2019/12/bavarian-order-of-merit-for-thomas-mueller | title = Thomas M\u00fcller awarded Bavarian Order of Merit  | website = FC Bayern Munich | date = 3 December 2019 | access-date = 3 December 2019}}</ref>\n*[[World Soccer Awards#World Player of the Year|World Soccer Young Player of the Year]]: 2010<ref name=\"WS2010\">{{cite web|url=http://www.worldsoccer.com/news/xavi-voted-world-soccer-player-of-the-year|title=Xavi voted World Soccer Player of the Year|publisher=[[World Soccer (magazine)|World Soccer]]|date=16 December 2010|accessdate=17 December 2010}}</ref>\n*[[Bravo Award]]: 2010<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rsssf.com/miscellaneous/bravo-awards.html|title=The Bravo Award|publisher=[[RSSSF]]|accessdate=13 February 2010}}</ref>\n*[[FIFA Ballon d'Or]]: [[2010 FIFA Ballon d'Or|15th place 2010]], [[2011 FIFA Ballon d'Or|13th place 2011]], [[2013 FIFA Ballon d'Or|17th place 2013]], [[2014 FIFA Ballon d'Or#FIFA Ballon d'Or 2014|5th place 2014]],<ref>{{cite web | title = FIFA Ballon d'Or 2014 \u2013 voting results | url = http://resources.fifa.com/mm/document/ballon-dor/general/02/50/58/59/fboaward_rankingpresslist2014_neutral.pdf | work = FIFA.com | format = PDF |date = 12 January 2015 | accessdate = 12 January 2015}}</ref> [[2015 FIFA Ballon d'Or#FIFA Ballon d'Or 2015|6th place 2015]]<ref>{{cite web | title = FIFA Ballon d'Or 2015 \u2013 voting results | url = http://resources.fifa.com/mm/document/ballon-dor/playeroftheyear-men/02/75/50/67/fboaward_rankingpresslist2015_neutral.pdf | work = FIFA.com | format = PDF |date = 12 January 2015 | accessdate = 12 January 2015}}</ref>\n*[[European Sports Media#ESM Team of the Year|ESM Team of the Year]]: 2012\u201313<ref name=\"kicker.de_2013\">{{cite web | url = http://www.kicker.de/news/fussball/intligen/startseite/543774/artikel_European-Sports-Magazines-Top-11.html | title = ESM-Top-11: Nur Torres und Ivanovic durchbrechen Bundesliga-Phalanx | language = German | publisher = kicker.de | date = 12 June 2013 | accessdate = 17 August 2014}}</ref>\n*[[UEFA Best Player in Europe Award]]: 2013 (6th place), 2014 (4th place), 2016 (10th place)\n*[[2015\u201316 UEFA Champions League|UEFA Champions League Team of the Group Stage]]: 2015<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/news/newsid=2317348.html#champions+league+team+group+stage|title= Champions League team of the group stage|publisher=[[UEFA]]|date=15 December 2015}}</ref>\n*[[FIFA World Cup awards#Golden Ball|FIFA World Cup Silver Ball]]: [[2014 FIFA World Cup|2014]]<ref name=FIFAWCSB&SB>{{cite web | url = https://www.fifa.com/worldcup/photos/galleries/y=2014/m=10/gallery=thomas-muller-receives-his-world-cup-awards-2454229.html | title = Thomas Muller receives his World Cup awards | website = FIFA.com | accessdate = 15 February 2018 | date = 6 October 2014 | quote = Thomas Mueller (C) receives the adidas silver Ball as second best player of the FIFA World Cup 2014\u2122 and the adidas silver boot for the second best goalscorer of the World Cup from Herbert Hainer, CEO adidas group (L) and his Brother Simon Mueller (R) at the adidas headquarter in Herzogenaurach. | publisher = F\u00e9d\u00e9ration Internationale de Football Association (FIFA)}}</ref><ref name=FIFAWCSB&SB2>{{cite web | url = https://www.fifa.com/worldcup/news/y=2014/m=10/news=muller-receives-world-cup-honours-2454235.html | title = Muller receives World Cup honours | website = FIFA.com | date = 6 October 2014 | accessdate = 15 February 2018 | publisher = F\u00e9d\u00e9ration Internationale de Football Association (FIFA) | quote = Muller was recognised by FIFA\u2019s Technical Study Group (TSG) for his impressive performances at the world\u2019s greatest football competition, receiving the adidas Silver Ball as the World Cup\u2019s second-best player. [...] With five goals and three assists, he also secured the adidas Silver Boot as the second-highest goalscorer at the 2014 World Cup, having previously won the Golden Boot in South Africa four years earlier.}}</ref>\n*[[FIFA World Cup awards#All-Star Team|FIFA World Cup All-Star Team]]: [[2014 FIFA World Cup|2014]]<ref>{{cite web | url = https://www.fifa.com/worldcup/statistics/castrol-index/top11.html | title = Castrol Index Top 11 | publisher = FIFA.com | accessdate = 17 August 2014}}</ref>\n*[[2014 FIFA World Cup awards#Dream Team|FIFA World Cup Dream Team]]: [[2014 FIFA World Cup|2014]]<ref>{{cite web | url = https://www.fifa.com/worldcup/games/dream-team/index.html | title = The Dream Team | publisher = FIFA.com | accessdate = 17 August 2014}}</ref>\n* [[FIFPro World XI]] 3rd team: 2014, 2015<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.fifpro.org/news/fifa-fifpro-world-xi-the-reserve-teams/en/ |title=FIFA FIFPro World XI: the reserve teams \u2013 FIFPro World Players' Union |publisher=FIFPro.org |date=15 January 2015 |access-date=1 October 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.fifpro.org/news/2015-world-xi-the-reserve-teams-2/en/ |title=2015 World XI: the Reserve Teams \u2013 FIFPro World Players' Union |publisher=FIFPro.org |date=11 January 2016 |access-date=1 October 2017}}</ref>\n* [[FIFPro World XI]] 5th team: 2016<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.fifpro.org/news/2016-world-11-the-reserve-teams/en/ |title=2016 World 11: the reserve teams \u2013 FIFPro World Players' Union |publisher=FIFPro.org |date=9 January 2017 |access-date=1 October 2017}}</ref>\n* [[DFB-Pokal]] top assist provider: [[2015\u201316 DFB-Pokal|2015\u201316]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.espnfc.com/german-dfb-pokal/2061/statistics/assists?season=2015 |title= German DFB Pokal Statistics \u2013 ESPN FC |publisher=ESPN FC |access-date=12 November 2017}}</ref>\n*Most [[FIFA World Cup]]s with at least five goals (2010\u20132014); record shared with [[Te\u00f3filo Cubillas]] (1970, 1978) & [[Miroslav Klose]] (2002\u20132006)\n* [[Bundesliga]] top assist provider: [[2017-18 Bundesliga|2017\u201318]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bundesliga.com/en/news/Bundesliga/lewandowski-thomas-muller-2017-18-most-goals-most-assists-top-stats-481046.jsp|title=Robert Lewandowski, Thomas M\u00fcller and the Bundesliga's 2017/18 chart-toppers|publisher=Bundesliga|accessdate=18 May 2018}}</ref>\n* [[Bundesliga]] Team of the Season: [[2017\u201318 Bundesliga|2017\u201318]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bundesliga.com/en/news/Bundesliga/fifa-18-ultimate-team-of-the-season-james-rodriguez-reus-lewandowski-pulisic-479371.jsp|title=CONFIRMED 2017/18 Bundesliga FIFA 18 Team of the Season|publisher=Bundesliga|accessdate=5 June 2018}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n*[[List of footballers with 100 or more caps]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category}}\n*{{Official website}} {{in lang|de}}\n*{{DFB|3249<!-- thomas-muller -->|Thomas Muller}}\n*{{fussballdaten}}\n*{{Soccerway}}\n*{{NFT player}}\n*{{FIFA player}}\n*{{UEFA player}}\n*{{ESPN FC}}\n\n{{FC Bayern Munich squad}}\n{{Navboxes\n|title= Germany squads\n|bg= white\n|fg= black\n|bordercolor= black\n|list1=\n{{Germany squad 2010 FIFA World Cup}}\n{{Germany squad UEFA Euro 2012}}\n{{Germany squad 2014 FIFA World Cup}}\n{{Germany squad UEFA Euro 2016}}\n{{Germany squad 2018 FIFA World Cup}}\n}}\n{{Navboxes\n|title=Awards\n|bg=gold\n|fg=navy\n|list1=\n{{2014 FIFA World Cup Team of the Tournament}}\n{{FIFA World Cup top scorers}}\n{{FIFA World Cup Best Young Player}}\n{{FIFA World Cup Silver Ball}}\n{{German Cup top scorers}}\n{{Bravo Award winners}}\n}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Muller, Thomas}}\n[[Category:1989 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Weilheim-Schongau]]\n[[Category:German Roman Catholics]]\n[[Category:Footballers from Bavaria]]\n[[Category:German footballers]]\n[[Category:Association football forwards]]\n[[Category:Association football midfielders]]\n[[Category:FC Bayern Munich II players]]\n[[Category:FC Bayern Munich footballers]]\n[[Category:Bundesliga players]]\n[[Category:3. Liga players]]\n[[Category:UEFA Champions League winning players]]\n[[Category:Germany youth international footballers]]\n[[Category:Germany under-21 international footballers]]\n[[Category:Germany international footballers]]\n[[Category:2010 FIFA World Cup players]]\n[[Category:UEFA Euro 2012 players]]\n[[Category:2014 FIFA World Cup players]]\n[[Category:UEFA Euro 2016 players]]\n[[Category:2018 FIFA World Cup players]]\n[[Category:FIFA World Cup-winning players]]\n[[Category:FIFA Century Club]]\n[[Category:Recipients of the Bavarian Order of Merit]]\n", "name_user": "Davykamanzi", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eStyle of play", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Thomas_M%C3%BCller"}
{"title_page": "Short Films by Louis C.K.", "text_new": "{{italic title}}\n\n'''''Short Films by Louis C.K.''''' (2001) is a [[DVD]] collection of nine early comedy short films by American comedian [[Louis C.K.]] made from 1990 to 2000.<ref>{{Cite web|url = https://web.archive.org/web/20011129220451/http://www.louisck.com/|title = Louie's Short Films DVD|date = 29 November 2001|access-date = 7 March 2020|website = [[Louisck]].com|publisher = Circus King Films|last = C.K.|first = Louis}}</ref>  All the films were written, directed, produced, and edited by C.K. with cinematography by Paul Koestner.<ref>{{Cite web|url = http://laughingsquid.com/louis-c-k-s-independent-short-films-1993-1999/|title = Louis C.K.\u2019s Independent Short Films (1993-1999)|date = 19 April 2013|access-date = 7 March 2020|website = [[Laughing Squid]]|publisher = |last = Blazenhoff|first = Rusty}}</ref>  The DVD was originally self-produced and self-released by his company Circus King Films on his website and then re-released in 2020, along with a digital download version.<ref>{{Cite web|url = https://louisck.com/collections/short-films-by-louis-c-k|title = Short Films by Louis C.K.|date = 2 March 2020|access-date = 7 March 2020|website = [[Louisck]].com|publisher = [[Pig Newton]]|last = C.K.|first = Louis}}</ref>\n\nThe only short films it excludes from that era are his very first amateur short film from 1984, ''Trash Day'', and two shorts featured on ''[[Late Night with Conan O'Brien]]'' as \"joke previews\": ''Searching for Nixon''<ref>{{Cite web|url = https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=1t_s0pTg_CA|title = Louis C.K. on Conan (1997-01-01)|date = 17 August 2015|access-date = 7 March 2020|website = [[YouTube]].com|publisher = [[Google]]}}</ref> in 1997 and ''Persona Ne'll Aqua''<ref>{{Cite web|url = https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=O6ql9SZMCiM|title = Persona Ne'll Aqua|date = 29 November 2006|access-date = 7 March 2020|website = [[YouTube]].com|publisher = [[Google]]}}</ref> from 1999.\n\nThe six short films in the collection that were made in 1995 were originally featured at that time on ''[[Howie Mandel's Sunny Skies]]'', then later re-copyrighted in 1998 and posted on [[YouTube]] by C.K. in 2006.  These films were executive produced by [[Howie Mandel]], produced by Nick Smith, with music by [[Mark Pender]], sound by Paul Bang and casting by Jennifer Sauer.<ref>{{Cite web|url = https://www.imdb.com/title/tt0234830/fullcredits?ref_=tt_cl_sm#cast|title = Howie Mandel's Sunny Skies (1995\u2013 ) Full Cast & Crew|date = 1995|access-date = 7 March 2020|website = [[IMDb]].com|publisher = [[Amazon]]}}</ref>\n\nThe extra features on the video include C.K.'s biography; a trailer to his feature film directorial debut, ''[[Tomorrow Night (film)|Tomorrow Night]]'' (1998); a video introduction to the films by C.K.; and more text information and credits of the films.<ref>{{Citation |title=Short Films by Louis C.K. |date=2001 |url=https://www.amazon.com/Short-Films-Louis-C-K-DVD/dp/B002F56M3C/ref=sr_1_1?dchild=1&keywords=short+films+of+Louis+ck&qid=1586247198&sr=8-1 |publisher=Circus King Films|access-date=March 7, 2020}}</ref>\n\nThe films are listed in the order they appear on the DVD.\n\n== ''Ice Cream'' ==\n{{Main|Ice Cream (1993 film)}}\n''Ice Cream'' (1993, 13 minutes, black & white) Featuring Laura Kightlinger, [[Craig Anton]], Rick Shapiro, Sheldon Wicowitz, Jim Labrioza, Mike Ivy, Louis C.K., Neal Brennan, Yvette Edelhart, Coby Schoffman, Chipps Cooney, William Milauskas and Bustamante-Azteca. Executive produced by David Campbell, Christine Martin and David Martin; Associate produced by Craig Anton and Lucien Hold. The film has been shown at the [[Museum of Modern Art]], [[Sundance Film Festival]], on [[PBS]] and C.K.'s [[YouTube]] channel in 2006.\n\n== ''Brunch'' ==\n''Brunch'' (1995, 4 minutes, color) A group of four ladies talk over brunch. Featuring Rick Shapiro as a woman and three other older actresses. Written with Rick Shapiro.\n\n== ''Hello There'' ==\n''Hello There'' (1995, 4 minutes and 20 seconds, black & white) A man played by [[Ron Lynch (comedian)|Ron Lynch]] uses a tape recorder to communicate. Also featuring Louis C.K. (as voice on tape and man on street), Gilda Conrad, Paul Kozlowski, Richard Abernathy and Cary Prusa. Written with Ron Lynch.\n\n== ''The Legend of Willie Brown'' ==\n''The Legend of Willie Brown'' (1995, 4 minutes, black & white/color) [[Mockumentary]] of a jazz musician. Featuring Larney Rutledge, Andre Blake, [[D. C. Benny]], [[Eddie Brill]] and [[William \"Mickey\" Stevenson]].\n\n== ''Highjacker'' ==\n''Highjacker'' (1995, 4 minutes and 23 seconds, color) A man played by Rick Shapiro tries to highjack the Staten Island ferry, mistakenly thinking it is a boat that can take him to Bolivia. Also featuring Todd Barry, [[Mike Bocchetti]], David Dean and Tony Devon. Sound by John Murphy.\n\n== ''The Letter V'' ==\n''The Letter V'' (1995, 4 minutes and 29 seconds, color) A man has much enthusiasm for and many struggles with the letter \"V\". Featuring [[Robert Smigel]], Nick Smith and Nancy Shane. Costumes by Bill Tull.\n\n== ''Guess Which Person is Crazy'' ==\n''Guess Which Person is Crazy'' (1995, 2 minutes, color)\n\n== ''Ugly Revenge'' ==\n''Ugly Revenge'' (2000, 6 minutes, black & white) Rival urban cowboys duke it out. Featuring [[Amy Poehler]], Ron Lynch, [[J. B. Smoove]], [[Tommy Blacha]] and Louis C.K. as narrator. The film has been shown on [[PBS]]'s ''ShortCuts'' program in 2000 which was hosted by C.K. and then he posted it on his YouTube channel in 2006.\n\n== ''Caesar's Salad'' ==\n''Caesar's Salad'' (1990, 27 minutes, color) A group of friends have an absurd, surrealist picnic in the park. Featuring [[Dave Allen (actor)|Dave Allen]], [[Dave Attell]], [[Todd Barry]], [[Neal Brennan]], [[Mark Cohen (comedian)|Mark Cohen]], Chipps Cooney, [[Nick Di Paolo]], [[Laura Kightlinger]], Christopher Nissley, [[Caroline Rhea]], [[Ray Romano]], [[Jeff Ross]], [[Rick Shapiro]], [[Sarah Silverman]], [[Chuck Sklar]] and Mike Sweeney. Music by [[Marc Maron]] (his scenes were cut, but his guitar is still heard).\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Louis C.K.}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Short Films by Louis C.K.}}\n[[Category:1990s films]]\n[[Category:1990s comedy films]]\n[[Category:1990s black comedy films]]\n[[Category:English-language films]]\n[[Category:American avant-garde and experimental films]]\n[[Category:American black-and-white films]]\n[[Category:American comedy films]]\n[[Category:American films]]\n[[Category:American independent films]]\n[[Category:American satirical films]]\n[[Category:American short films]]\n[[Category:Films directed by Louis C.K.]]\n[[Category:Films set in New York City]]\n[[Category:Films shot in New York (state)]]\n[[Category:Films shot in New York City]]\n[[Category:Films with screenplays by Louis C.K.]]\n[[Category:Home video releases]]\n[[Category:Short film compilations]]\n", "text_old": "{{italic title}}\n\n'''''Short Films by Louis C.K.''''' (2001) is a [[DVD]] collection of nine early comedy short films by American comedian [[Louis C.K.]] made from 1990 to 2000.<ref>{{Cite web|url = https://web.archive.org/web/20011129220451/http://www.louisck.com/|title = Louie's Short Films DVD|date = 29 November 2001|access-date = 7 March 2020|website = [[Louisck]].com|publisher = Circus King Films|last = C.K.|first = Louis}}</ref>  All the films were written, directed, produced, and edited by C.K. with cinematography by Paul Koestner.<ref>{{Cite web|url = http://laughingsquid.com/louis-c-k-s-independent-short-films-1993-1999/|title = Louis C.K.\u2019s Independent Short Films (1993-1999)|date = 19 April 2013|access-date = 7 March 2020|website = [[Laughing Squid]]|publisher = |last = Blazenhoff|first = Rusty}}</ref>  The DVD was originally self-produced and self-released by his company Circus King Films on his website and then re-released in 2020, along with a digital download version.<ref>{{Cite web|url = https://louisck.com/collections/short-films-by-louis-c-k|title = Short Films by Louis C.K.|date = 2 March 2020|access-date = 7 March 2020|website = [[Louisck]].com|publisher = [[Pig Newton]]|last = C.K.|first = Louis}}</ref>\n\nThe only short films it excludes from that era are his very first amateur short film from 1984, ''Trash Day'', and two shorts featured on ''[[Late Night with Conan O'Brien]]'' as \"joke previews\": ''Searching for Nixon''<ref>{{Cite web|url = https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=1t_s0pTg_CA|title = Louis C.K. on Conan (1997-01-01)|date = 17 August 2015|access-date = 7 March 2020|website = [[YouTube]].com|publisher = [[Google]]}}</ref> in 1997 and ''Persona Ne'll Aqua''<ref>{{Cite web|url = https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=O6ql9SZMCiM|title = Persona Ne'll Aqua|date = 29 November 2006|access-date = 7 March 2020|website = [[YouTube]].com|publisher = [[Google]]}}</ref> from 1999.\n\nThe six short films in the collection that were made in 1995 were originally featured at that time on ''[[Howie Mandel's Sunny Skies]]'', then later re-copyrighted in 1998 and posted on [[YouTube]] by C.K. in 2006.  These films were executive produced by [[Howie Mandel]], produced by Nick Smith, with music by [[Mark Pender]], sound by Paul Bang and casting by Jennifer Sauer.<ref>{{Cite web|url = https://www.imdb.com/title/tt0234830/fullcredits?ref_=tt_cl_sm#cast|title = Howie Mandel's Sunny Skies (1995\u2013 ) Full Cast & Crew|date = 1995|access-date = 7 March 2020|website = [[IMDb]].com|publisher = [[Amazon]]}}</ref>\n\nThe extra features on the video include C.K.'s biography, a trailer to his feature film directorial debut, ''[[Tomorrow Night (film)|Tomorrow Night]]'' (1998), a video introduction to the films by C.K. and more text information and credits of the films.<ref>{{Citation |title=Short Films by Louis C.K. |date=2001 |url=https://www.amazon.com/Short-Films-Louis-C-K-DVD/dp/B002F56M3C/ref=sr_1_1?dchild=1&keywords=short+films+of+Louis+ck&qid=1586247198&sr=8-1 |publisher=Circus King Films|access-date=March 7, 2020}}</ref>\n\nThe films are listed in the order they appear on the DVD.\n\n== ''Ice Cream'' ==\n{{Main|Ice Cream (1993 film)}}\n''Ice Cream'' (1993, 13 minutes, black & white) Featuring Laura Kightlinger, [[Craig Anton]], Rick Shapiro, Sheldon Wicowitz, Jim Labrioza, Mike Ivy, Louis C.K., Neal Brennan, Yvette Edelhart, Coby Schoffman, Chipps Cooney, William Milauskas and Bustamante-Azteca. Executive produced by David Campbell, Christine Martin and David Martin; Associate produced by Craig Anton and Lucien Hold. The film has been shown at the [[Museum of Modern Art]], [[Sundance Film Festival]], on [[PBS]] and C.K.'s [[YouTube]] channel in 2006.\n\n== ''Brunch'' ==\n''Brunch'' (1995, 4 minutes, color) A group of four ladies talk over brunch. Featuring Rick Shapiro as a woman and three other older actresses. Written with Rick Shapiro.\n\n== ''Hello There'' ==\n''Hello There'' (1995, 4 minutes and 20 seconds, black & white) A man played by [[Ron Lynch (comedian)|Ron Lynch]] uses a tape recorder to communicate. Also featuring Louis C.K. (as voice on tape and man on street), Gilda Conrad, Paul Kozlowski, Richard Abernathy and Cary Prusa. Written with Ron Lynch.\n\n== ''The Legend of Willie Brown'' ==\n''The Legend of Willie Brown'' (1995, 4 minutes, black & white/color) [[Mockumentary]] of a jazz musician. Featuring Larney Rutledge, Andre Blake, [[D. C. Benny]], [[Eddie Brill]] and [[William \"Mickey\" Stevenson]].\n\n== ''Highjacker'' ==\n''Highjacker'' (1995, 4 minutes and 23 seconds, color) A man played by Rick Shapiro tries to highjack the Staten Island ferry, mistakenly thinking it is a boat that can take him to Bolivia. Also featuring Todd Barry, [[Mike Bocchetti]], David Dean and Tony Devon. Sound by John Murphy.\n\n== ''The Letter V'' ==\n''The Letter V'' (1995, 4 minutes and 29 seconds, color) A man has much enthusiasm for and many struggles with the letter \"V\". Featuring [[Robert Smigel]], Nick Smith and Nancy Shane. Costumes by Bill Tull.\n\n== ''Guess Which Person is Crazy'' ==\n''Guess Which Person is Crazy'' (1995, 2 minutes, color)\n\n== ''Ugly Revenge'' ==\n''Ugly Revenge'' (2000, 6 minutes, black & white) Rival urban cowboys duke it out. Featuring [[Amy Poehler]], Ron Lynch, [[J. B. Smoove]], [[Tommy Blacha]] and Louis C.K. as narrator. The film has been shown on [[PBS]]'s ''ShortCuts'' program in 2000 which was hosted by C.K. and then he posted it on his YouTube channel in 2006.\n\n== ''Caesar's Salad'' ==\n''Caesar's Salad'' (1990, 27 minutes, color) A group of friends have an absurd, surrealist picnic in the park. Featuring [[Dave Allen (actor)|Dave Allen]], [[Dave Attell]], [[Todd Barry]], [[Neal Brennan]], [[Mark Cohen (comedian)|Mark Cohen]], Chipps Cooney, [[Nick Di Paolo]], [[Laura Kightlinger]], Christopher Nissley, [[Caroline Rhea]], [[Ray Romano]], [[Jeff Ross]], [[Rick Shapiro]], [[Sarah Silverman]], [[Chuck Sklar]] and Mike Sweeney. Music by [[Marc Maron]] (his scenes were cut, but his guitar is still heard).\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Louis C.K.}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Short Films by Louis C.K.}}\n[[Category:1990s films]]\n[[Category:1990s comedy films]]\n[[Category:1990s black comedy films]]\n[[Category:English-language films]]\n[[Category:American avant-garde and experimental films]]\n[[Category:American black-and-white films]]\n[[Category:American comedy films]]\n[[Category:American films]]\n[[Category:American independent films]]\n[[Category:American satirical films]]\n[[Category:American short films]]\n[[Category:Films directed by Louis C.K.]]\n[[Category:Films set in New York City]]\n[[Category:Films shot in New York (state)]]\n[[Category:Films shot in New York City]]\n[[Category:Films with screenplays by Louis C.K.]]\n[[Category:Home video releases]]\n[[Category:Short film compilations]]\n", "name_user": "Sjur03", "label": "safe", "comment": "fixed grammar", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Short_Films_by_Louis_C.K."}
{"title_page": "Sky Atlantic", "text_new": "{{EngvarB|date=June 2014}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2017}}\n{{Infobox television channel\n| name              = Sky Atlantic\n| logofile          = Sky Atlantic 2020.png\n| logosize          = 250px\n| logocaption       = \n| logoalt           = \n| launch            = {{Start date and age|df=yes|2011|2|1}}\n| closed date       = \n| replaced names    = [[Channel One (UK and Ireland)|Channel One]]\n| share            = 0.22% (Including +1)\n| share as of      = {{Start date|df=yes|2020|3|22}}\n| share source     = [https://www.barb.co.uk/viewing-data/weekly-viewing-summary-new/ BARB]\n| picture format    = [[2160p]] [[UHDTV]]<br />{{small|(downscaled to [[1080i]] and [[16:9]] [[576i]] for the [[HDTV]] and [[SDTV]] feeds, respectively)}}\n| network           = \n| owner             = [[Sky Ltd|Sky]]\n| slogan            = The Home of World Class Television<ref name=\"THOWCT\" />/The Home of HBO<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=t1E9BLeXIRE&t=0m58s|title=Sky Atlantic UK|work=British Sky Broadcasting|publisher=YouTube|date=23 December 2010}}</ref>/Let The Stories Begin\n| country           = {{Plainlist|\n* [[United Kingdom]]\n* [[Republic of Ireland|Ireland]]\n}}\n| language          = English\n| broadcast area    = {{Plainlist|\n* United Kingdom\n* Ireland\n}}\n| sister names      = [[Challenge (TV channel)|Challenge]]<br>[[Pick (TV channel)|Pick]]<br>[[Sky One]]<br>[[Sky Two]]<br>[[Sky Arts]]<br>[[Sky Cinema]]<br>[[Sky Comedy]]<br>[[Sky Crime]]<br>[[Sky News]]<br>[[Sky Sports]]<br>[[Sky Box Office|Sky Sports Box Office]]<br>[[Sky Sports F1]]<br>[[Sky Sports News]]<br>[[Sky Sports Racing]]<br>[[Sky Witness (TV channel)|Sky Witness]]\n| t\n| timeshift names   = Sky Atlantic +1\n| web               = [http://skyatlantic.sky.com/ skyatlantic.sky.com]\n| sat serv 1        = [[Sky plc|Sky]]\n| sat chan 1        = Channel 108 (SD/HD)<br />Channel 208 (+1)<br />Channel 808 (SD)<br />[[On Demand (Sky)|On Demand]]\n| cable serv 1      = \n| cable chan 1      = \n| iptv serv 1       = [[BT TV]] (via [[Now TV (Sky)|Now TV]])\n| iptv chan 1       = Channel 342<br>Channel 357 (HD)\n| online serv 1     = [[Sky Go]]\n| online chan 1     = [http://go.sky.com/ Watch live] {{nowrap|(UK and Ireland only)}}\n| online serv 2   = [[Now TV (Sky)|Now TV]]\n| online chan 2   = [http://www.nowtv.com/ Watch live] (UK and Ireland only)\n|}}\n\n'''Sky Atlantic''' is a British [[pay television]] channel owned by [[Sky (company)|Sky Limited]]. The channel is primarily dedicated to imported programmes from the United States, and holds the domestic rights to [[HBO]] and [[Showtime (TV network)|Showtime]] dramas along with other original series.\n\n[[Sky Deutschland]] broadcasts a [[Sky Atlantic (Germany)|German-language version]] of the channel in Germany and Austria, while [[Sky Italia]] broadcasts an [[Sky Atlantic (Italy)|Italian-language version]] of the channel in Italy. Their programming is also dominated by HBO and Showtime series, usually dubbed in the domestic language. The German and Italian channels also premiere Sky Originals produced in their countries, like ''[[Das Boot (TV series)|Das Boot]]'' in Germany and ''[[The Young Pope]]'' and ''[[Gomorrah (TV series)|Gomorrah]]'' in Italy.\n\n==Background==\nSky Atlantic launched on 1 February 2011 on [[Sky plc|Sky]] in the United Kingdom and Ireland.<ref name=\"THOWCT\">{{cite web|url=http://tv.sky.com/skyatlantic|title=Sky Atlantic: The Home of World Class Television|publisher=[[Sky plc|British Sky Broadcasting]]|date=23 December 2010}}</ref><ref name=\"Launch BSkyB\">{{cite web|url=http://corporate.sky.com/page.aspx?pointerid=e9bfe9c2636c4ec28f66aea2494770f1|title=Sky Atlantic HD is new home of HBO & Mad Men|publisher=British Sky Broadcasting|date=1 October 2010}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.rte.ie/ten/2011/0201/skyatlantic.html|title=Sky Atlantic to launch today|date=1 February 2011|work=RT\u00c9 News|accessdate=1 February 2011}}</ref> Separated channels with the same name operate in [[Germany]], [[Austria]] and [[Italy]].\n\nSky Atlantic is available in both [[Standard-definition television|standard definition]] and [[High-definition television|high definition]], the latter on '''Sky Atlantic HD'''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/broadcasting/news/a279695/sky-to-launch-sky-atlantic-channel.html|title=Sky to launch Sky Atlantic channel|publisher=Digital Spy|date=1 October 2010}}</ref> [[Stuart Murphy]] extended his responsibilities to become director of programmes for [[Sky One]], [[Sky Two]], [[Pick (TV channel)|Pick]] and Sky Atlantic.<ref name=\"Launch BSkyB\" /> On 5 May 2011, Elaine Pyke, the head of drama at Sky, was promoted to director of Sky Atlantic, reporting to Murphy.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/media/2011/may/05/bskyb-elaine-pyke-sky-atlantic|title=BSkyB promotes Elaine Pyke to Sky Atlantic director|publisher=The Guardian|date=5 May 2011|location=London|first=Mark|last=Sweney}}</ref>\n\nProgrammes on the channel are also offered to Sky customers via on-demand channels including the [[On Demand (Sky)|On Demand]] and [[Sky Go]] services and Now TV. Both [[BT TV]] and [[Virgin Media]] had held talks with Sky over the new channel but have been unable to agree a carriage deal,<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/business/news/rivals-miss-out-as-sky-launches-atlantic-channel-2177090.html|title=Rivals miss out as Sky launches Atlantic channel|publisher=The Independent|date=6 January 2011|location=London}}</ref> in Virgin's case due to pricing.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/broadcasting/news/a302145/virgin-media-to-miss-out-on-sky-atlantic.html|title=Virgin Media to miss out on Sky Atlantic|publisher=Digital Spy|date=4 February 2011}}</ref>\n\nIt was announced on 25 October 2010 that Sky Atlantic would launch on Sky channel 108, which was previously occupied by [[Pick (TV channel)|Sky 3]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://corporate.sky.com/investors/press_releases/2010/Sky_confirms_strengthened_line_up.htm|title=Sky confirms strengthened entertainment line-up|date=25 October 2010|work=[[Sky plc|British Sky Broadcasting]]|accessdate=25 October 2010}}</ref> Sky Atlantic also utilises the HD swap bouquet system developed by Sky, which switches SD channels with HD channels for HD Pack subscribers, meaning Sky Atlantic HD is on channel 108 and the standard definition version appears on channel 808.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/broadcasting/news/a296093/sky-atlantic-to-launch-next-month.html|title=Sky Atlantic to launch next month|publisher=Digital Spy|date=5 January 2011}}</ref>\n\n===Sky Atlantic +1===\nA one-hour [[timeshift channel|timeshift]] of Sky Atlantic started broadcasting on 20 September 2012 on channel 173.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.imediamonkey.com/2012/09/04/sky-atlantic-1-launching-september-20th/|title=Sky Atlantic +1 launching, September 20th|publisher=imediamonkey|date=4 September 2012|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140203072149/http://www.imediamonkey.com/2012/09/04/sky-atlantic-1-launching-september-20th/|archivedate=3 February 2014|df=dmy-all}}</ref> It moved to channel 170 on 9 June 2015 as part of a reshuffle which also included the closure of [[Sky 3D]], Sky Livingit becoming [[Real Lives (TV channel)|Real Lives]] and Sky Arts 1 and Sky Arts 2 merging to become simply [[Sky Arts]]. It moved to channel 217 on 18 July 2017 as part of the [[Sky Sports]] reshuffle which included Sky Sports Mix moving to entertainment, and again to 208 on 1 May 2018 as part of Sky's major EPG reshuffle due to Sky Atlantic being channel 108.\n\n==Programming==\nSky Atlantic relies heavily on screenings of US television programmes, with 50% of all programming coming from [[HBO]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/media/2011/jan/31/sky-atlantic-new-tv-channel|title=BSkyB bets on Sky Atlantic to boost subscriber numbers|publisher=The Guardian|date=31 January 2011|location=London|first=Matt|last=Baker}}</ref> Although the channel mainly screens dramas, there are blocks in the schedule dedicated to comedies and movies<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.skymedia.co.uk/_downloads/823/Sky%20Atlantic%20HD-%20no%20logos%20%28W%29.pdf|title=Welcome to Sky Atlantic HD|date=16 November 2010|publisher=Sky Media|format=PDF}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.skyprogrammeinformation.co.uk/download/February%20Sky%20Atlantic.pdf|title=Programme Information Highlights; February Sky Atlantic|date=21 December 2010|publisher=Sky Programme Information|format=PDF}}</ref> The launch of Sky Atlantic followed the broadcaster's \u00a3150m,<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/media/2010/oct/01/bskyb-sky-atlantic-mad-men|title=BSkyB to launch Sky Atlantic|publisher=guardian.co.uk|date=1 October 2010|location=London|first=Mark|last=Sweney}}</ref> five-year deal to buy exclusive UK and Irish TV rights to HBO's entire archive, new HBO programming and a first-look deal on all co-productions.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://corporate.sky.com/media/press_releases/2010/HBO.htm|title=Sky agrees output deal to become the UK home of HBO|publisher=British Sky Broadcasting|date=29 July 2010}}</ref>\n\nIn January 2016, Sky expanded the portfolio shown on Atlantic, after purchasing exclusive rights to Showtime programming; however, Sky does not have rights to all Showtime programmes, as some of the shows are aired on [[Channel 4]].\n\nBy 2020, with Sky now owned by NBCUniversal, some of the HBO shows were re-distributed for re-run on the other NBCUniversal channels on Sky, such as series 1 & 2 of Westworld on SyFy, and some of the HBO comedy was moved over to the Sky Comedy channel, such as Avenue 5 and Veep.\n\n===First run US programmes===\n\n*''[[Ballers]]''\n*''[[Barry (TV series)|Barry]]''\n*''[[Big Little Lies (TV series)|Big Little Lies]]''\n*''[[Billions (TV series)|Billions]]''\n*''[[Boardwalk Empire]]''\n*''[[The Brink (TV series)|The Brink]]''\n*''[[Camping (U.S. TV series)|Camping]]''\n*''[[Crashing (U.S. TV series)|Crashing]]''\n*''[[The Deuce (TV series)|The Deuce]]\n*''[[Divorce (TV series)|Divorce]]''\n*''[[Euphoria (American TV series)|Euphoria]]''\n*''[[Game of Thrones]]''\n*''[[Hello Ladies]]''\n*''[[Mosaic (murder mystery)|Mosaic]]\n*''[[Ray Donovan]]''\n*''[[Silicon Valley (TV series)|Silicon Valley]]''\n*''[[Succession (TV series)|Succession]]\n*''[[True Detective]]\n*''[[Westworld (TV series)|Westworld]]\n*''[[Watchmen (TV series)|Watchmen]]\n*''[[Veep]]''\n\n===Original programming===\nFor Sky Atlantic original programmes produced in Germany see [[Sky Atlantic (Germany)]] and in Italy see [[Sky Atlantic (Italy)]].\n*''[[Britannia (TV series)|Britannia]]'' \u2013 Co-production with [[Prime Video|Amazon Prime Video]]\n*''[[Camping (UK TV series)|Camping]]''\n*''[[Chernobyl (miniseries)|Chernobyl]]'' \u2013 Co-production with [[HBO]]\n*''[[Fortitude (TV series)|Fortitude]]''\n*''[[Hit & Miss]]''\n*''[[Hunderby]]''\n*''[[The Last Panthers]]'' \u2013 Co-production with [[Canal+]]\n*''[[Mr. Sloane]]''\n*''[[Patrick Melrose (TV series)|Patrick Melrose]]'' \u2013 Co-production with [[Showtime (TV network)|Showtime]]\n*''[[Penny Dreadful (TV series)|Penny Dreadful]]'' \u2013 Co-production with [[Showtime (TV network)|Showtime]]\n*''[[Riviera (TV series)|Riviera]]''\n*''[[Save Me (UK TV series)|Save Me]]''\n*''[[Sally4Ever]]'' \u2013 Co-production with [[HBO]]\n*''[[Tin Star (TV series)|Tin Star]]''\n*''[[The Tunnel (TV series)|The Tunnel]]'' \u2013 Co-production with [[Canal+]]\n\n===Most watched programmes===\nThe following is a list of the ten most watched programmes on Sky Atlantic (all of them being episodes of ''Game of Thrones''), based on Live +7 data supplied by [[Broadcasters' Audience Research Board|BARB]] up to 20 May 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.barb.co.uk/viewing-data/four-screen-dashboard/|title=Four-screen dashboard {{!}} BARB|website=www.barb.co.uk|language=en-GB|access-date=25 July 2017}}</ref> The number of viewers does not include repeats or Irish ratings. Additionally, all of these episodes were the most viewed programme of the week on non-terrestrial television in the UK. Game of Thrones is Sky's most popular show.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/media/2016/jul/06/game-of-thrones-most-popular-sky-series-ever-as-16m-download-show|title=Game of Thrones most popular Sky series ever with 5m viewers|last=|first=|date=2016-07-06|work=The Guardian|access-date=2019-05-09}}</ref>\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Rank\n! Programme\n! Episode\n! Number of Viewers\n! Date\n|-\n|1\n| rowspan=\"10\" |''[[Game of Thrones]]''\n|8.04 \u2013 [[The Last of the Starks]]\n|5,430,451\n|6 May 2019\n|-\n|2\n|8.02 \u2013 [[A Knight of the Seven Kingdoms (Game of Thrones)|A Knight of the Seven Kingdoms]]\n|5,266,034\n|22 April 2019\n|-\n|4\n|8.05 \u2013 [[The Bells (Game of Thrones)|The Bells]]\n|5,039,355\n|13 May 2019\n|-\n|3\n|8.06 \u2013 [[The Iron Throne (Game of Thrones)|The Iron Throne]] \n|5,011,277\n|20 May 2019\n|-\n|5\n|8.03 \u2013 [[The Long Night (Game of Thrones)|The Long Night]]\n|4,983,910\n|29 April 2019\n|-\n|6\n|8.01 \u2013 [[Winterfell (Game of Thrones episode)|Winterfell]]\n|4,380,834\n|15 April 2019\n|-\n|7\n|7.07 \u2013 [[The Dragon and the Wolf]]\n|3,535,000\n|28 August 2017\n|-\n|8 ||7.01 \u2013 [[Dragonstone (Game of Thrones)|Dragonstone]]||3,487,000 ||17 July 2017\n|-\n|9\n|7.05 \u2013 [[Eastwatch]]\n|3,420,000\n|14 August 2017\n|-\n| 10 || 7.03 \u2013 [[The Queen's Justice]]|| 3,263,000 || 31 July 2017\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{official website|http://skyatlantic.sky.com/}}\n\n{{Sky Atlantic}}\n{{Sky Ltd}}\n{{Media in the United Kingdom|television}}\n{{Television in Ireland}}\n\n[[Category:Sky television channels]]\n[[Category:Television channels and stations established in 2011]]\n[[Category:2011 establishments in the United Kingdom]]\n[[Category:English-language television stations in the United Kingdom]]\n[[Category:Television channels in the United Kingdom]]\n", "text_old": "{{EngvarB|date=June 2014}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2017}}\n{{Infobox television channel\n| name              = Sky Atlantic\n| logofile          = Sky Atlantic - Logo 2018.svg\n| logosize          = 250px\n| logocaption       = \n| logoalt           = \n| launch            = {{Start date and age|df=yes|2011|2|1}}\n| closed date       = \n| replaced names    = [[Channel One (UK and Ireland)|Channel One]]\n| share            = 0.22% (Including +1)\n| share as of      = {{Start date|df=yes|2020|3|22}}\n| share source     = [https://www.barb.co.uk/viewing-data/weekly-viewing-summary-new/ BARB]\n| picture format    = [[2160p]] [[UHDTV]]<br />{{small|(downscaled to [[1080i]] and [[16:9]] [[576i]] for the [[HDTV]] and [[SDTV]] feeds, respectively)}}\n| network           = \n| owner             = [[Sky Ltd|Sky]]\n| slogan            = The Home of World Class Television<ref name=\"THOWCT\" />/The Home of HBO<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=t1E9BLeXIRE&t=0m58s|title=Sky Atlantic UK|work=British Sky Broadcasting|publisher=YouTube|date=23 December 2010}}</ref>/Let The Stories Begin\n| country           = {{Plainlist|\n* [[United Kingdom]]\n* [[Republic of Ireland|Ireland]]\n}}\n| language          = English\n| broadcast area    = {{Plainlist|\n* United Kingdom\n* Ireland\n}}\n| sister names      = [[Challenge (TV channel)|Challenge]]<br>[[Pick (TV channel)|Pick]]<br>[[Sky One]]<br>[[Sky Two]]<br>[[Sky Arts]]<br>[[Sky Cinema]]<br>[[Sky Comedy]]<br>[[Sky Crime]]<br>[[Sky News]]<br>[[Sky Sports]]<br>[[Sky Box Office|Sky Sports Box Office]]<br>[[Sky Sports F1]]<br>[[Sky Sports News]]<br>[[Sky Sports Racing]]<br>[[Sky Witness (TV channel)|Sky Witness]]\n| t\n| timeshift names   = Sky Atlantic +1\n| web               = [http://skyatlantic.sky.com/ skyatlantic.sky.com]\n| sat serv 1        = [[Sky plc|Sky]]\n| sat chan 1        = Channel 108 (SD/HD)<br />Channel 208 (+1)<br />Channel 808 (SD)<br />[[On Demand (Sky)|On Demand]]\n| cable serv 1      = \n| cable chan 1      = \n| iptv serv 1       = [[BT TV]] (via [[Now TV (Sky)|Now TV]])\n| iptv chan 1       = Channel 342<br>Channel 357 (HD)\n| online serv 1     = [[Sky Go]]\n| online chan 1     = [http://go.sky.com/ Watch live] {{nowrap|(UK and Ireland only)}}\n| online serv 2   = [[Now TV (Sky)|Now TV]]\n| online chan 2   = [http://www.nowtv.com/ Watch live] (UK and Ireland only)\n|}}\n\n'''Sky Atlantic''' is a British [[pay television]] channel owned by [[Sky (company)|Sky Limited]]. The channel is primarily dedicated to imported programmes from the United States, and holds the domestic rights to [[HBO]] and [[Showtime (TV network)|Showtime]] dramas along with other original series.\n\n[[Sky Deutschland]] broadcasts a [[Sky Atlantic (Germany)|German-language version]] of the channel in Germany and Austria, while [[Sky Italia]] broadcasts an [[Sky Atlantic (Italy)|Italian-language version]] of the channel in Italy. Their programming is also dominated by HBO and Showtime series, usually dubbed in the domestic language. The German and Italian channels also premiere Sky Originals produced in their countries, like ''[[Das Boot (TV series)|Das Boot]]'' in Germany and ''[[The Young Pope]]'' and ''[[Gomorrah (TV series)|Gomorrah]]'' in Italy.\n\n==Background==\nSky Atlantic launched on 1 February 2011 on [[Sky plc|Sky]] in the United Kingdom and Ireland.<ref name=\"THOWCT\">{{cite web|url=http://tv.sky.com/skyatlantic|title=Sky Atlantic: The Home of World Class Television|publisher=[[Sky plc|British Sky Broadcasting]]|date=23 December 2010}}</ref><ref name=\"Launch BSkyB\">{{cite web|url=http://corporate.sky.com/page.aspx?pointerid=e9bfe9c2636c4ec28f66aea2494770f1|title=Sky Atlantic HD is new home of HBO & Mad Men|publisher=British Sky Broadcasting|date=1 October 2010}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.rte.ie/ten/2011/0201/skyatlantic.html|title=Sky Atlantic to launch today|date=1 February 2011|work=RT\u00c9 News|accessdate=1 February 2011}}</ref> Separated channels with the same name operate in [[Germany]], [[Austria]] and [[Italy]].\n\nSky Atlantic is available in both [[Standard-definition television|standard definition]] and [[High-definition television|high definition]], the latter on '''Sky Atlantic HD'''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/broadcasting/news/a279695/sky-to-launch-sky-atlantic-channel.html|title=Sky to launch Sky Atlantic channel|publisher=Digital Spy|date=1 October 2010}}</ref> [[Stuart Murphy]] extended his responsibilities to become director of programmes for [[Sky One]], [[Sky Two]], [[Pick (TV channel)|Pick]] and Sky Atlantic.<ref name=\"Launch BSkyB\" /> On 5 May 2011, Elaine Pyke, the head of drama at Sky, was promoted to director of Sky Atlantic, reporting to Murphy.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/media/2011/may/05/bskyb-elaine-pyke-sky-atlantic|title=BSkyB promotes Elaine Pyke to Sky Atlantic director|publisher=The Guardian|date=5 May 2011|location=London|first=Mark|last=Sweney}}</ref>\n\nProgrammes on the channel are also offered to Sky customers via on-demand channels including the [[On Demand (Sky)|On Demand]] and [[Sky Go]] services and Now TV. Both [[BT TV]] and [[Virgin Media]] had held talks with Sky over the new channel but have been unable to agree a carriage deal,<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/business/news/rivals-miss-out-as-sky-launches-atlantic-channel-2177090.html|title=Rivals miss out as Sky launches Atlantic channel|publisher=The Independent|date=6 January 2011|location=London}}</ref> in Virgin's case due to pricing.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/broadcasting/news/a302145/virgin-media-to-miss-out-on-sky-atlantic.html|title=Virgin Media to miss out on Sky Atlantic|publisher=Digital Spy|date=4 February 2011}}</ref>\n\nIt was announced on 25 October 2010 that Sky Atlantic would launch on Sky channel 108, which was previously occupied by [[Pick (TV channel)|Sky 3]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://corporate.sky.com/investors/press_releases/2010/Sky_confirms_strengthened_line_up.htm|title=Sky confirms strengthened entertainment line-up|date=25 October 2010|work=[[Sky plc|British Sky Broadcasting]]|accessdate=25 October 2010}}</ref> Sky Atlantic also utilises the HD swap bouquet system developed by Sky, which switches SD channels with HD channels for HD Pack subscribers, meaning Sky Atlantic HD is on channel 108 and the standard definition version appears on channel 808.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/broadcasting/news/a296093/sky-atlantic-to-launch-next-month.html|title=Sky Atlantic to launch next month|publisher=Digital Spy|date=5 January 2011}}</ref>\n\n===Sky Atlantic +1===\nA one-hour [[timeshift channel|timeshift]] of Sky Atlantic started broadcasting on 20 September 2012 on channel 173.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.imediamonkey.com/2012/09/04/sky-atlantic-1-launching-september-20th/|title=Sky Atlantic +1 launching, September 20th|publisher=imediamonkey|date=4 September 2012|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140203072149/http://www.imediamonkey.com/2012/09/04/sky-atlantic-1-launching-september-20th/|archivedate=3 February 2014|df=dmy-all}}</ref> It moved to channel 170 on 9 June 2015 as part of a reshuffle which also included the closure of [[Sky 3D]], Sky Livingit becoming [[Real Lives (TV channel)|Real Lives]] and Sky Arts 1 and Sky Arts 2 merging to become simply [[Sky Arts]]. It moved to channel 217 on 18 July 2017 as part of the [[Sky Sports]] reshuffle which included Sky Sports Mix moving to entertainment, and again to 208 on 1 May 2018 as part of Sky's major EPG reshuffle due to Sky Atlantic being channel 108.\n\n==Programming==\nSky Atlantic relies heavily on screenings of US television programmes, with 50% of all programming coming from [[HBO]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/media/2011/jan/31/sky-atlantic-new-tv-channel|title=BSkyB bets on Sky Atlantic to boost subscriber numbers|publisher=The Guardian|date=31 January 2011|location=London|first=Matt|last=Baker}}</ref> Although the channel mainly screens dramas, there are blocks in the schedule dedicated to comedies and movies<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.skymedia.co.uk/_downloads/823/Sky%20Atlantic%20HD-%20no%20logos%20%28W%29.pdf|title=Welcome to Sky Atlantic HD|date=16 November 2010|publisher=Sky Media|format=PDF}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.skyprogrammeinformation.co.uk/download/February%20Sky%20Atlantic.pdf|title=Programme Information Highlights; February Sky Atlantic|date=21 December 2010|publisher=Sky Programme Information|format=PDF}}</ref> The launch of Sky Atlantic followed the broadcaster's \u00a3150m,<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/media/2010/oct/01/bskyb-sky-atlantic-mad-men|title=BSkyB to launch Sky Atlantic|publisher=guardian.co.uk|date=1 October 2010|location=London|first=Mark|last=Sweney}}</ref> five-year deal to buy exclusive UK and Irish TV rights to HBO's entire archive, new HBO programming and a first-look deal on all co-productions.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://corporate.sky.com/media/press_releases/2010/HBO.htm|title=Sky agrees output deal to become the UK home of HBO|publisher=British Sky Broadcasting|date=29 July 2010}}</ref>\n\nIn January 2016, Sky expanded the portfolio shown on Atlantic, after purchasing exclusive rights to Showtime programming; however, Sky does not have rights to all Showtime programmes, as some of the shows are aired on [[Channel 4]].\n\nBy 2020, with Sky now owned by NBCUniversal, some of the HBO shows were re-distributed for re-run on the other NBCUniversal channels on Sky, such as series 1 & 2 of Westworld on SyFy, and some of the HBO comedy was moved over to the Sky Comedy channel, such as Avenue 5 and Veep.\n\n===First run US programmes===\n\n*''[[Ballers]]''\n*''[[Barry (TV series)|Barry]]''\n*''[[Big Little Lies (TV series)|Big Little Lies]]''\n*''[[Billions (TV series)|Billions]]''\n*''[[Boardwalk Empire]]''\n*''[[The Brink (TV series)|The Brink]]''\n*''[[Camping (U.S. TV series)|Camping]]''\n*''[[Crashing (U.S. TV series)|Crashing]]''\n*''[[The Deuce (TV series)|The Deuce]]\n*''[[Divorce (TV series)|Divorce]]''\n*''[[Euphoria (American TV series)|Euphoria]]''\n*''[[Game of Thrones]]''\n*''[[Hello Ladies]]''\n*''[[Mosaic (murder mystery)|Mosaic]]\n*''[[Ray Donovan]]''\n*''[[Silicon Valley (TV series)|Silicon Valley]]''\n*''[[Succession (TV series)|Succession]]\n*''[[True Detective]]\n*''[[Westworld (TV series)|Westworld]]\n*''[[Watchmen (TV series)|Watchmen]]\n*''[[Veep]]''\n\n===Original programming===\nFor Sky Atlantic original programmes produced in Germany see [[Sky Atlantic (Germany)]] and in Italy see [[Sky Atlantic (Italy)]].\n*''[[Britannia (TV series)|Britannia]]'' \u2013 Co-production with [[Prime Video|Amazon Prime Video]]\n*''[[Camping (UK TV series)|Camping]]''\n*''[[Chernobyl (miniseries)|Chernobyl]]'' \u2013 Co-production with [[HBO]]\n*''[[Fortitude (TV series)|Fortitude]]''\n*''[[Hit & Miss]]''\n*''[[Hunderby]]''\n*''[[The Last Panthers]]'' \u2013 Co-production with [[Canal+]]\n*''[[Mr. Sloane]]''\n*''[[Patrick Melrose (TV series)|Patrick Melrose]]'' \u2013 Co-production with [[Showtime (TV network)|Showtime]]\n*''[[Penny Dreadful (TV series)|Penny Dreadful]]'' \u2013 Co-production with [[Showtime (TV network)|Showtime]]\n*''[[Riviera (TV series)|Riviera]]''\n*''[[Save Me (UK TV series)|Save Me]]''\n*''[[Sally4Ever]]'' \u2013 Co-production with [[HBO]]\n*''[[Tin Star (TV series)|Tin Star]]''\n*''[[The Tunnel (TV series)|The Tunnel]]'' \u2013 Co-production with [[Canal+]]\n\n===Most watched programmes===\nThe following is a list of the ten most watched programmes on Sky Atlantic (all of them being episodes of ''Game of Thrones''), based on Live +7 data supplied by [[Broadcasters' Audience Research Board|BARB]] up to 20 May 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.barb.co.uk/viewing-data/four-screen-dashboard/|title=Four-screen dashboard {{!}} BARB|website=www.barb.co.uk|language=en-GB|access-date=25 July 2017}}</ref> The number of viewers does not include repeats or Irish ratings. Additionally, all of these episodes were the most viewed programme of the week on non-terrestrial television in the UK. Game of Thrones is Sky's most popular show.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/media/2016/jul/06/game-of-thrones-most-popular-sky-series-ever-as-16m-download-show|title=Game of Thrones most popular Sky series ever with 5m viewers|last=|first=|date=2016-07-06|work=The Guardian|access-date=2019-05-09}}</ref>\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Rank\n! Programme\n! Episode\n! Number of Viewers\n! Date\n|-\n|1\n| rowspan=\"10\" |''[[Game of Thrones]]''\n|8.04 \u2013 [[The Last of the Starks]]\n|5,430,451\n|6 May 2019\n|-\n|2\n|8.02 \u2013 [[A Knight of the Seven Kingdoms (Game of Thrones)|A Knight of the Seven Kingdoms]]\n|5,266,034\n|22 April 2019\n|-\n|4\n|8.05 \u2013 [[The Bells (Game of Thrones)|The Bells]]\n|5,039,355\n|13 May 2019\n|-\n|3\n|8.06 \u2013 [[The Iron Throne (Game of Thrones)|The Iron Throne]] \n|5,011,277\n|20 May 2019\n|-\n|5\n|8.03 \u2013 [[The Long Night (Game of Thrones)|The Long Night]]\n|4,983,910\n|29 April 2019\n|-\n|6\n|8.01 \u2013 [[Winterfell (Game of Thrones episode)|Winterfell]]\n|4,380,834\n|15 April 2019\n|-\n|7\n|7.07 \u2013 [[The Dragon and the Wolf]]\n|3,535,000\n|28 August 2017\n|-\n|8 ||7.01 \u2013 [[Dragonstone (Game of Thrones)|Dragonstone]]||3,487,000 ||17 July 2017\n|-\n|9\n|7.05 \u2013 [[Eastwatch]]\n|3,420,000\n|14 August 2017\n|-\n| 10 || 7.03 \u2013 [[The Queen's Justice]]|| 3,263,000 || 31 July 2017\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{official website|http://skyatlantic.sky.com/}}\n\n{{Sky Atlantic}}\n{{Sky Ltd}}\n{{Media in the United Kingdom|television}}\n{{Television in Ireland}}\n\n[[Category:Sky television channels]]\n[[Category:Television channels and stations established in 2011]]\n[[Category:2011 establishments in the United Kingdom]]\n[[Category:English-language television stations in the United Kingdom]]\n[[Category:Television channels in the United Kingdom]]\n", "name_user": "Conor M98", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sky_Atlantic"}
{"title_page": "Likir", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2018}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=May 2018}}\n{{Infobox settlement\n| name                    = Likir\n| native_name             =\n| native_name_lang        =\n| settlement_type         = Village\n| image_skyline           = Likir Gompa.jpg\n| image_alt               =\n| image_caption           = [[Likir Monastery|Klu-kkhyil monastery]]\n| etymology               =\n| pushpin_map             = India Ladakh#India\n| pushpin_map_caption     = Location in Ladakh, India\n| coordinates             = {{coord|34.2903203|N|77.2132106|E|display=inline,title}}\n| coordinates_footnotes   =\n| subdivision_type        = Country\n| subdivision_name        = [[India]]\n| subdivision_type1 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 = [[States and union territories of India|Union Territory]]\n| subdivision_name1 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 = [[Ladakh]]\n| subdivision_type2       = [[List of districts of India|District]]\n| subdivision_name2       = [[Leh district|Leh]]\n| subdivision_type3       = [[Tehsil]]\n| subdivision_name3       = Likir<ref>https://leh.nic.in/about-district/administrative-setup/village/</ref>\n| established_title       =\n| established_date        =\n| founder                 =\n| seat_type               = [[Panchayat]]\n| seat                    =\n| leader_party            =\n| leader_title            =\n| leader_name             =\n| unit_pref               = Metric\n| area_total_km2          =\n| elevation_m             = 3651\n| population_as_of        = 2011\n| population_total        = 1058\n| population_density_km2  = auto\n| population_demonym      =\n| timezone1               = [[Indian Standard Time|IST]]\n| utc_offset1             = +5:30\n| postal_code_type        = <!-- [[Postal Index Number|PIN]] -->\n| postal_code             =\n| area_code_type          = <!-- [[Telephone numbers in India|STD Code]] -->\n| area_code               =\n| blank_name_sec1         = [[2011 Census of India|2011 census]] code\n| blank_info_sec1         = 848\n| footnotes               =\n}}\n\n'''Likir''' is a village and headquarter of [[eponymous]] [[Leh_district#subdivision|Subdivision]] in the [[Leh district]] of [[Ladakh]], [[India]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://leh.nic.in/depts/villageamenitydirectory.pdf |title=Blockwise Village Amenity Directory |publisher=Ladakh Autonomous Hill Development Council |accessdate=2015-07-23 }}</ref><ref name=lehdiv4>[https://leh.nic.in/about-district/administrative-setup/tehsil/ Leh tehsils].</ref> It is located in the Likir [[tehsil]], in the [[Ladakh]] region. [[Khalatse]] is a nearby trekking place.<ref>[http://www.pbase.com/robert_michael/20040721]</ref>\n\nIt is famous for the nearby Klu-kkhyil (meaning \"water spirits\") [[gompa]] (Buddhist monastery). The [[Likir Monastery]] was first built in the 11th century and was rebuilt in the 18th century, and currently has a {{convert|25|ft|m|adj=mid|-tall}} gold-covered [[Buddharupa|Buddha statue]]. It is occupied by monks of the [[Geluk]]pa order. It is located 52&nbsp;km from [[Leh]].\n\n==Demographics==\nAccording to the [[2011 census of India]], Likir has 218 households. The effective literacy rate (i.e. the literacy rate of population excluding children aged 6 and below) is 72.93%.<ref name=\"census_2011\"/>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|+ Demographics (2011 Census)<ref name=\"census_2011\">{{cite news |url=http://www.censusindia.gov.in/datagov/CDB_PCA_Census/PCA_CDB_0103_F_Census.xls |title=Leh district census |work=[[2011 Census of India]] |publisher=Directorate of Census Operations |accessdate=2015-07-23 }}</ref>\n! !! Total !! Male !! Female\n|-\n| Population || 1058 || 573 || 485\n|-\n| Children aged below 6 years || 105 || 57 || 48\n|-\n| [[Scheduled caste]] || 0 || 0 || 0\n|-\n| [[Scheduled tribe]] || 1056 || 572 || 484\n|-\n| Literates || 695 || 432 || 263\n|-\n| Workers (all) || 299 || 211 || 88\n|-\n| Main workers (total) || 255 || 194 || 61\n|-\n| Main workers: Cultivators || 141 || 12